    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-03-19T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-19T19:00:00-05:00" n="349"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/3–1648: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Guatemala</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-03-19T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 19, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>116. Deep concern is felt by Dept over reports indicating official Guatemalan
                    arms and ammunition being used in Costa Rica (San José telegram to Dept, No 98,
                    March 18<note n="1" xml:id="d349fn1">Not printed.</note>). You are requested to
                    seek early interview with President Arévalo in order to refer to these reports
                    and obtain statement Guatemalan position. In this connection Dept refers again
                    to <gloss target="#t_Depcirtel1">Depcirtel</gloss> Jan 17.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thorp</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
